Get ready to start the game!

Thank you for reading the instructions. Get ready start with the 40 rounds of this game.

If you need to take a break, feel free to take one after the end of a round, before continuing to the next one.

Remember, the more money the spider gets, the bigger your bonus will be!

Press space to begin.


(If, at any point, the space key does not take you to the next page, click once on the text and try again.)

response.Q0: Using the node inspector, I would first look at the values of the nodes that are the furthest (at the edge). If I found a node that was at least $60-$88, especially the ones above $80, I would stop inspecting and start moving the spider. This is because I realized the first few nodes didn't carry much weight. So, even if there were negative ones, I would still make a greater profit if I went for the furthest node (the ones with $60-$88).
response.Q1: Yes, at first I would just randomly inspect the first nodes, the ones closest to me. But overtime, I realized I could make more money if I paid more attention to the nodes at the edges.
response.Q2: On a scale of 1-10? I would say maybe a 6. The difficulty lied in the fact that I did not really know what came next. I had to guess, with the help of the node inspector of course.

I absolutely loved this game. I will admit, at first I wasn't looking forward to the 40 rounds. But as I played more and more, the 40 rounds started to feel a bit small. I wanted more. That's how much I enjoyed. Looking forward to working with you again, should a second version be released.
